"```sql\nSELECT \n  Laboratory.Date AS LaboratoryDate, \n  (YEAR(Patient.First Date) - YEAR(Patient.Birthday)) AS AgeAtFirstVisit\nFROM \n  Patient\nJOIN \n  Examination ON Patient.ID = Examination.ID\nJOIN \n  Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE \n  Examination.Diagnosis = 'SjS'\nORDER BY \n  Patient.Birthday ASC, Laboratory.Date DESC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the date of the oldest SjS patient's laboratory work and calculates the age of the patient when they initially arrived at the hospital. It joins the `Patient`, `Examination`, and `Laboratory` tables, filters for patients diagnosed with SjS, and orders by the oldest birthday and the most recent laboratory date."